    Yahoo News 360

    AI resurrection: Creepy or comforting?

    Those who are suffering loss might come to depend on AI avatars as stand-ins, prolonging their grief.

    People have long placed emotional value on likenesses and relics as means of keeping the dead with them.

    Theres the potential for chatbots to completely misrepresent what people wouldve said for themselves.

    Deepfake reanimations are part of an ongoing exchange between our relationship to death and our visualizing technologies.

    It may well become difficult, if not impossible, to ensure that we are remembered through purely analog means.
